==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pleasing
<hw>Pleas"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Giving pleasure or satisfaction;
causing agreeable emotion; agreeable; delightful; <as>as, a
<ex>pleasing</ex> prospect; <ex>pleasing</ex> manners.</as></def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pleasing</xex> harmony.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pleasing</xex> features.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Macaulay.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Pleas"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pleas"ing*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Gratifying; delightful; agreeable. See
<er>Pleasant</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pleasing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pleasing
<hw>Pleas"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An object of pleasure.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pleasurable</ent>⟦br⟧
